I am a cinematographer based in Mumbai, India. I has been working in the Indian film industry in Mumbai for the last twenty one years. My lighting is lyrical and every composition tells a tale of emotions.  I graduated from Film & TV Institute of India, Pune in 1992, which is one of premier film schools of Asia.

I am documentary filmmaker. I have worked widely in the field of generating non-fiction content for various international broadcasters. My last assignment was with the National Geographic Channel where I headed local productions for Colours India, National Geographics and Fox Traveller.  

I have been a photographer for almost as long as I can remember. My obsession with the Himalayas started twelve years ago, when I first stumbled upon the untapped beauty of the mountains with a borrowed point-and-shoot camera, six rolls of film and hardly enough clothes to keep myself warm. 

I have worked with all the major lifestyle TV channels as a Documentary Filmmaker, Network Producer and Creative Director. Until very recently, I was a Network Executive Producer with National Geographic Channel and have worked on most of their adventure reality programs, like Mission Army, Trapped in Ladakh, etc.

After having a twelve year career in television, I started doing timelapse photography full time in 2012. While in TV, I generated non-fiction content for various broadcasters like Colors, Sony, Doscovery, National Geographhic Channel, Fox Traveller, etc. My last corporate job was with Nat Geo where I was heading local productions for Nat Geo and Fox Traveller. \n\nYou could call me someone who specializes in \\Timelapse\\" photography. Timelapse is a novel technique of filming in which rather than filming \\"real time\\"
profile_color: we film the very elements of time. These elements generally are the movements of the following: Sun
column22: etc. By doing this we capture a very dynamic nature of time which completely redefines a location. The resulting visuals are stunning and captures the attention of audience because of the \\"novelty\\" in them."

Doing what I love and loving what I do. I am a social worker who is often mistaken as a film maker or a photographer. I am now comfortable with that. Having found  (actually I want to say awakened but for the risk of sounding presumptuous, I am avoiding that word here.. . or have I?)  the purpose and the theme of my life, I am spared from the pain of aimlessness and endowed with the joy of purposefulness.

I have never deliberately avoided any kind of work but definitely vigorously pursued the kind of work that I felt can contribute to - humankind's shared project to create the future--a project in which anyone anywhere can participate and which lays the solid foundations for a sustainable global society  these words are from the 2014 Peace Proposal written by my mentor.

Be it photography or motion picture, one question I ask myself each time I pick up the camera  is this for the love of the people? and when the answer from my heart is yes, then I know its time to take the step forward without fear.

My Timelapse journey began with a phone call from Anurag Jetly, while I was in Amritsar. I had just returned from the Golden Temple and was on a cycle rickshaw, when Anurag called me for the first time and asked if I had made anything like a Timelapse Silder. I told him that I had been meaning to do just that for a while , but had not found the impetus to do it. He told me that he was leaving on a shooting trip to Ladakh and Spiti and he'd delay the trip if I could make a slider that he could take. I asked him for a month and asked him if I could accompany him on the trip. 

A month later we were bouncing and sliding through the water swept rocks and rubble roads of the Spiti valley in a Wagon R. The journey was underway.

As you can gather I make my own equipment (www.embracecinema.com). My first personal foray into timelapse photography was in the Andamans, when over a new year vacation I undertook the first series of shots. After that I shot in Kerala and Banaras. After that I made another trip to Spiti. 

I can confidentially say that after Anurag I am the second most accomplished timelapse professional in the country. I have recently shot for Rakeysh Omprakash Mehra for his new film. I've also been selected by Prasanna Vithanage, the Sri Lankan filmmaking master, to do timelapses for his next film.

To every project i bring my arsenal of equipment, which includes 4 axes of movement - Slider, Tilt, Pan and Focus or Zoom, a multitude of cameras and lenses and about 3-4 years of experience. I've recently custom built a new device that can shoot timelapses with forward motion without a slider, thereby achieving a shot that has thus far never been seen. I am also experimenting with Virtual Reality, Timelapse in Virtual Reality and Timelapse in VR in 3D.

As you can guess I'm a proud man and technician, please approach me with a grace and courtesy you'd reserve for yourself . A lot of people think they understand timelapse photography, very few do. I am still learning, and there's a way to go. Let my work speak for me.

Nakul Sood is the son of an ex-naval officer and a triple masters degree holding mother. He was born a quite happy child. He had a very vivid imagination and a lot of fun as a child, though he was solitary even then. At the age of twelve he went to Doon School, the years were formative in a loose sense. 

In his early twenties he went to New York to study film and returned to India in 2002, whereupon he began a career as a documentary cameraperson. 

Nakul is currently manufacturing items for video and audio recording, his products can be seen at www.embracecinema.com. 

Aside from his business, Nakul has an over-arching theory for human behaviour that he doesn't hesitate to share with anyone who starts a serious conversation. He is a keen collector of films, and often still works as a cameraperson. He also harbours a desire to make films and has been working towards that end. He also believes human life to be a spiritual process.

Vipin Heero is a singer, songwriter and composer with a unique style of his own. He has carved a niche for himself with the cute and funny songs he has created. While some of them are humorous romantic songs, others are based on interesting observations from life. For example, he sings about the fear of lizards, or a fathers expectations from his son, or about auto rickshaw walas, or stressful corporate life, but each time presenting these in a way that is guaranteed to bring a smile to your face. He is trained in classical guitar, and his sense of music is fabulous. He is also an actor and has appeared on television.

Pandit Arnab Chatterjee was born and groomed in a  musical ambience amidst nature in the suburban town of Basirhat, near Kolkata. Initiated into music at the early age of five by his  father Sangeetachariya Late Sree Arun Kr Chatterjee, a learned musician of the Kirana Gharana, Arnab was later groomed by none other than Late Pandit A. Kanan and Vidushi Malabika Kanan.Arnab flowered into a young performer very early in his life. At the age of seven years only, he shared a platform with Ustad Amjad Ali Khan at Suresh Sangeet Sammelan,Kolkata in the year 1979.ITC S.R.A.Sangeet Sammelan  `81 saw him as a nine year old performer bursting with Confidence.Securing top position in competitions has been his way of life. A  recipient of the National Talent Scholarship, Arnab won the gold medal along with the Degree of Sangeet Visharad by securing the  first position. As an `A` grade performer of All India Radio &  Doordarshan Kolkata, he broadcasts classical recitals regularly  and has raised high hopes among the music lovers and experts. He has performed severally at The National Programme of Music broadcasted at  ALL INDIA RADIO. The Sursingar Samad, Mumbai, bestowed him with the Title of `Surmani. Arnab was an ex-scholar of ITC-SRA,KOLKATA,and has also studied under the guidance of Late Pandit A Kanan and Vidushi Malabika  Kanan and Ustad Mashkoor Ali Khan .He has been selected and being empanelled as an artist of Hindustani classical music(vocal) by (ICCR).  Arnab stood the first position in All India Music Competition organized by Pandit Omkarnath Thakur Sangeet Mondal, Bharuch,  Gujrat in the year2002.Now he is attached with Rabindra Bharati University, Bengal Music College Under the University of kolkata  and Vishwa Varati Shantiniketan as an external Examiner of Classical Vocal Music on regular basis.BHARATIYA SANSKRITI  SAMSAD,KOLKATA,awarded him as a Best vocalist for the year 2005. Arnab Chatterjee was deputed at Indira Gandhi Cultural Centre,  Dhaka, Bangladesh as Hindustani Vocal Music trainer cum performer by ICCR, Govt. of India since Feb,2010 to Feb,2012. He has number  of students at India and abroad who are acclaimed as good performer in the field of Hindustani Classical Vocal Music. Besides his Career in Music Arnab Chatterjee passed the graduation in Economics from the University of kolkata. At present Pandit Arnab Chatterjee is a one of the most acclaimed vocalist in the scenario of Hindustani Classical music.He is maintaining the pure tradition of Kirana Gharana with mixing the other forms of gayaki both in Khyal and Thumri which makes his presentation very colorful and popular .He has able to established himself as a  self identical and a very popular vocalist of India.\n

about_us:
A graceful Kathak dancer who possesses a sound sense of rhythm, understanding of the complexities of Talas,
has a feeling for music and  a creative ability to express herself through the language of movement. Sampada was initiated into Kathak at 6 yrs of age and is an alumni of Kala Academy, Goa having trained under Guru Smt. Amala Suri Patkar. 

Having successfully completed the Parangat diploma in Kathak at Kala Academy, Sampada moved to Pune and came under the tutelage of renowned Kathak legend late Pandita Dr. Rohini Bhate at Nrityabharati Kathak Dance Academy. 

In 2012 Sampada settled in Bangalore and established RIDDHAM  Kathak School where she aims to create an awareness on this dance form and train her disciples to the best of her ability. Riddham is located in Yelahanka New Town.

Sampada has many solo and group performances to her credits such as performances in the dance festivals at Somnathpur and Halebid-Belur in Karnataka, Nakshatra Utsav, Goa, Nimhan dance festival, Madhya Pradesh to name a few. She has been the lead artiste for all productions of Kala Academy Goa such Kathak Panorama, Krishna Leela, Bharat Darshan and various Kathak choreographies. She has worked in association with German artistes and the fusion choreography titled Music from Air and Water received much acclaim in Goa. In Pune, she has performed through the Nrityabharati group performances. Sampada has co-choreographed a short film- Radha Bhakti Sudha in 2007 which received the Jurys Special Mention Award at the New York Short Film. In Bangalore she has performed in the prestigious World Dance Day 2015 and 2016 curated by Prof. Ashish Mohan Khokar.

Sampada brings forth a repertoire in the Lucknow-Jaipur gharana of Kathak as established by Guru Rohini ji.

I am recognised as a senior master musician living in the holy city of Varanasi, U.P, India. I have been a professional musician for over 40 years and sought after artist and teacher in the field of Indian classical music, both in my beloved hometown Varanasi and the rest of the world.

I am known for my knowledge of ragas and talas, allowing me to go deep into both commonly performed ragas, as well as the very rare ones. I have learnt instrumental and vocal music from different gharanas and styles, and perform in sitar as well as in surbahar.

I have regularly toured in the United States (1999, 2001, 2005, 2006, 2008, 2011), frequently appearing at colleges and universities where I have taught classes, given demonstrations, and offered concerts. I am a regular on All India Radio and Television (Grade A), and I have performed in concerts and festivals across the country. I have been a private teacher of sitar and surbahar for nearly forty years, teaching hundreds of students at a variety of institutions in Varanasi. These include Alliance for Global Education, Banaras Hindu University, Central University of Tibetan Studies , Five College Tibetan Studies in India Program, University of Wisconsins College Year in India Program and Where There be Dragons.

Sharanya Chandran is a contemporary example of a classical dancer trained in both the Guru-Shishya Parampara and the Parivaar Parampara.
Daughter and disciple of (Padmashri) Smt. Geeta Chandran, Sharanya has been learning Bharatanatyam from the age of four. She began learning both from her mother and Guru K N Dakshinamurthi and presented her formal solo debut performance, the Arangetram, in New Delhi in November 2001, at the age of 13. It is her continued passion to learn, invent and conceptualize new additions to the classical dance repertoire
Sharanya is the Vice President of the Natya Vriksha, an organization aimed at the preservation and promotion of Indian culture and dance. She is an integral part of Natya Vriksha Dance Company as a senior dancer and choreographer. She also assists with cultural management, curating festivals & events and media outreach.
Sharanya is empanelled with the Indian Council for Cultural Relations (ICCR) as a solo artist and is also nationally graded by Doordarshan.

Sharanya has performed to diverse audiences in India and overseas across multiple festivals and forums  both as a soloist and in group choreographies as part of the Natya Vriksha Dance Company. Some of the choreographies she has been a part of are: Sivam, Pratidhwani, Seasons (Bharatanatyam performed to the western classical musical score by Tchaikovsky), Mythologies Retold, Sankriti and Awakening
Some of her recent solo performances were for Natya Vrikshas Young Dancers Festival (as part of the World Dance Day celebration in 2014), the multifarious Monte Music (and dance) Festival, Goa in 2014, Vasuki Natyashalas Yuvanotsav young dancers festival in 2013, HCL Concert Series in 2012, Kuchipudi Dance Academys Vriddhi Dance Extraordinaire in 2012 and Guru Shovana Narayans Lalit Arpan Dance Festival in 2011.  

Across the years, Sharanya has performed in several major group productions across Indias best festivals such as the Ananya Dance Festival, 16th National Festival of Creative Arts, Pravasi Bharatiya Divas, Taj Mahotsav, Sankatmochan Music and Dance festival, Ananda Mahotsav, India International Film Fest, Sharad Poornima Festival, Delhi International Arts Festival, National Choreography Festival and Pandit Birju Maharajs Sadhana Festival.

Sharanya has taken part in performances across the world, including at the Lincoln Centre in New York (as part of Incredible India @ 60 festival); for the Thai Cultural Festival at the Thai Cultural Centre, Bangkok; at Queen Elizabeth Hall, London, to celebrate the 60th anniversary of the Indian Republic under the auspices of the Indian High Commission; the 8th World Hindi Conference in New York; solo dance recital at the Nehru Centre (London) and was part of ICCRs dance tour to Australia (Nattuvangam) ­ to name only a few. She also assisted in a Bharatanatyam workshop organized by the Bhartiya Vidya Bhawan, London.
Sharanya has also extensively used dance as a medium for social change through message oriented performances - on important social issues such as gender inequality, Female Foeticide, drug abuse, peace and harmony. She has also been involved in several Lecture Demonstrations for SPIC MACAY to spread awareness of the arts across school children across Uttar Pradesh, Assam, Meghalaya, Punjab, Delhi, Haryana, Uttaranchal, Odisha and Rajasthan
Sharanya enjoys teaching and engaging with young students at Natya Vriksha. Extensively trained in Nattuvangam, she supports Guru Geeta Chandran and Natya Vriksha through Nattuvangam (cymbals). She is also trained in Carnatic Vocal and is passionate about classical music.

In addition to her pursuit of her strong passion in the performing arts, Sharanya has an exceptional academic record, which exhibits her multi-dimensional personality. Having pursued her Bachelors in Economics from Delhi Universitys prestigious Lady Shri Ram College, Sharanya completed her Masters in Development Studies from the London School of Economics & Political Science in 2010 as a fully funded INLAKS scholar.
Concurrently, Sharanya is a development and policy expert. She is the Policy Manager at J-PAL (the Abdul Latif Jameel Poverty Action Lab) - South Asia, where she helps promote policy initiatives in the development sector. Sharanya was previously the Principal Consultant at the National Skill Development Agency, Ministry of Finance, Government of India (formerly the office of Advisor to the Prime Minister on the PMs National Council on Skill Development). Sharanya was nominated to be part of the Global Shapers Community, a youth initiative of the World Economic Forum and was also the Curator of the New Delhi Hub of the Community in 2013-14.
Endowed with a sparkling stage persona, Sharanyas natural flair for Bharatanatyams different facets of rhythm and expression make her a dancer to watch

(Padmashri) Geeta Chandran Dancer/Choreographer A celebrated artist and a star-performer, GeetaChandran is synonymous with the Indian classical dance: Bharatanatyam. She began learning Bharatanatyam from the tender age of 5 years under the tutelage of Smt. SwarnaSaraswathy, who hailed from the traditional Thanjavoordevadasiparampara. Subsequently, Geeta continued learning diverse aspects of the classical dance from a galaxy of eminent Gurus. 

Today she is a renowned artist who has synthesised the knowledge she received from her Gurus to imprint Bharatanatyam with her personal vision of the dance. In her dance presentations GeetaChandran skilfully weaves abstract notions of Joy, Beauty, Values, Aspirations, Myth and Spirituality.

Geeta is celebrated not only for her deep and composite understanding of the art of Bharatanatyam, but also for her Carnatic music (she is a trained and accomplished vocalist), her work in television, video and film, theatre, choreography, dance education, dance activism and dance-issue journalism.

Founder-President of Natya-Vriksha, an organization devoted to promoting Bharatanatyam, Geeta has evolved a holistic style of teaching the classical dance which engages young learners. She has presented the arangetrams (debut performance) of 30 senior disciples who continue their training under her and she continues to mentor over one hundred disciples; several of her students have blossomed as full-fledged performers. 

GeetaChandran is also Artistic Director of the NatyaVriksha Dance Company, known for the high aesthetic quality of its group presentations. 

Geeta has constantly striven to create new spaces for the classical dancer of today. She has continuously attempted to push the frontiers of the classical art and to reach out to new, and especially young, audiences. Geeta believes that dance must be linked to life and that artists must use their unique position in society to make a difference to life and living. Her choreographies HER VOICE and IMAGINING PEACE articulated her conviction that dance can be a vehicle to build social bridges. Her widely acclaimed dance-theatre production KAIKEYI and her choreographies on the themes of DRUGS have thrown the spotlight on issues of social stigma. Her 2008 work -- MYTHOLOGIES RETOLD -- addresses the social curse of female feticide. She is also known for using classical Bharatanatyam to amplify gender and environmental issues. 

An A-Top graded dancer at Doordarshan and at the Indian Council for Cultural Relations (ICCR), Geeta has been recipient of both the Junior and Senior Research Fellowships from the Government of Indias Department of Culture. She is recipient of several awards including the Lady Shri Ram College Illustrious Alumna Award, the DandayudhapaniPillai Award, the Bharat Nirman Award, the NatyaIlavarasi, the Indira Priyadarshini Award, the Media India Award, the National Critics Award, the Sringar Mani and the NatyaRatna. 

She has travelled all over the world with her performances and has danced at many prestigious dance festivals in India and abroad. In 2007, she was invited to perform at the World Hindi Conference in New York, and then again to represent India at the India-60 celebrations at the Lincoln Centre in New York.

Geeta is associated with several NGOs and charitable organizations raising resources for valuable causes, among them peace, environment and peace. She is well-known for her association with philanthropic causes, and has presented innumerable performances to raise funds for worth social causes. She is most especially identified with gender issues and poverty. Her recent work showcasing the horror of female feticide through dance has won her renewed praise. 

Geeta has authored a book SO MANY JOURNEYS, an intensely personal collection of her writings narrating her engagement with Bharatanatyam. In April 2009, in her book entitled Dynamic Women Dancers (Womens Hall of Fame series) Canadian author Anne Dublin listed GeetaChandran as one of ten global all time great dancers. 

A widely respected role model for the young generation, Geeta is on the Board of reputed educational institutions of India, both schools and colleges. She has also been nominated as a Board Member of Indias National Film Censor Board. She engages in the widest range of dance-related activities: performing, teaching, conducting, singing, collaborating, organizing, writing and speaking to new youth audiences. 

In recognition of her vast and varied contribution to Bharatanatyam, Geeta was awarded the prestigious national award -- the Padma Shri -- by the President of India in 2007. 

PS: According to a public youth poll conducted by Times of India in August 2008, GeetaChandran was voted Delhis hottest dancer.

Jagdeep Singh Bedi is a renowned Sitar and Surbahar player, who was initiated into music by his father, Shri Tara Singh Bedi who himself is a well known Sitar and Surbahar player. Jagdeeps Skills were later honed and developed by the reputed Sitar Guru, Shri Anil Dhar who imparted the intricacies of Sitar and Surbahar in the Senia Gharana style.

Jagdeep is known for his excellence in both Sitar and Surbahar and over the years, Jagdeep has proved his mettle giving stellar performances at leading musical venues in the country and abroad. He is empanelled with the Indian Council for Cultural Relations and is an accredited and acclaimed soloist with All India Radio.

As a mark of his outstanding ability to play both instruments, Music of the World-USA released an exclusive audio-cassette titled Soft and True which has been released worldwide. Jagdeep continues in his pursuit of music with single-minded devotion and humility.

An excellent blend of sensuous movement and graceful footwork with absolute control on Laya  That describes the performance of Moumala Nayak, an accomplished artiste of the Lucknow gharana of Kathak, and disciple of great Kathak Maestro Pt. Birju Maharaj. Daughter of Retired Principal Chief Engineer (DOT, BSNL Ministry of Communication) and belonging to amateur Magician parents, Moumala started learning Kathak in 1982 at the age of nine years from Shri Nagendra Prasad Mohini in Patna and acquired her M.A. in the same from Prayag Sangeet Samiti, Allahabad. She got her specialized advance training in Delhi under Smt. Vaswati Mishra and later under Kathak legend Pt. Birju Maharaj Completed Diploma Honours from National Institute of Kathak Dance, New Delhi.


Academically a topper in her school & college, Moumala has done various institutional courses in allied subjects with distinction namely in Hindustani Vocal Classical Music, Tabla, Painting, Russian Language, Reiki, Computer Science, Dress-designing etc. Her poetic and literary creativity is reflected in her compositions on classical music, musical scripts, essays, poems published in famous magazines and books. Her interest and creativity spread in all such fields of art complimentary to classical dance.

Sraboni, one of the leading thumri and ghazal exponents of today, is a disciple of the

legendary thumri singer, late Smt Shobha Gurtu. Sraboni has also received the guidance of

Pandit Dinkar Kaikini and Pandit Ajoy Chakraborty.

Sraboni has performed at several prestigious music festivals including the Kesarbai Kerkar

Sangeet Samaroh held by Kala Academy, Goa, Alladiya Khan Punyatithi Samaroh in

Mumbai and Swararpan (a tribute to Begum Akhtar) held by Sangeet Natak Akademi in

Delhi. She has also been a part of the Khazana Festival of Ghazals on numerous occasions,

performing with several prominent ghazal artistes like Pankaj Udhas, Anup Jalota, Talat Aziz

and Bhupinder & Mitali Singh. Sraboni also featured in the International Kite Festival held in

Ahmedabad where she shared the stage with Suresh Wadkar. Besides, Sraboni has

conducted a music appreciation course for the Indian Music Group at St Xaviers College in

Mumbai.

Sraboni has had the rare privilege of being part of a musical ensemble led by the tabla

legend Ustad Zakir Hussain on two occasions under the Aadi Anant Festival held by NCPA

in Mumbai and Delhi in 2013.

Sraboni has also performed at international cultural festivals such as those in Jordan,

Palestine, Qatar, Egypt and Zimbabwe through Indian Council of Cultural Relations as a

member of a troupe lead by Ms Prachee Shah (Kathak).

Sraboni's debut solo album "Thumri se ghazal tak" (https://itunes.apple.com/in/album/thumri-

se-ghazal- tak/id918605535) was released on 1st August 2014 at the Khazana Festival of

Ghazals by stalwarts of the ghazal world. Sraboni has also rendered her voice to the bhajan

CD album "Krishnarupa" which was released in September 2013

(https://www.oklisten.com/album/krisnaruupa/aaj_prabhu_mohey).

Sraboni holds a Masters Degree in Economics from the University of Mumbai and was

formerly "Lecturer in Charge" of the Department of Economics at Sophia College, Mumbai.

Sharon Lowen is a renowned artist of Odissi. She has bridged cultures performing on every continent as well as for television and film. Sharon has made her home in India since 1973 to dedicate herself to her work as an artist and to promote excellence in Indian performing arts.  She first came to India as a Fulbright Scholar with B.A. and M.A. degrees in Humanities, Fine Arts, Asian Studies and Dance from the University of Michigan.  Sharon received her training in Odissi from Padma Vibhushan Kelucharan Mohapatra, the undisputed master and architect of the contemporary Odissi repertoire.  Sharon Lowen, although an American by birth, has now been considered as a dancer who has shown with total conviction how dance is a language away and above any barrier of race and nationality.  Her performances are spiritually rich and of a high aesthetic order, praised for grace and superb abhinaya.
  
Sharon has performed throughout India and the United States, Canada, Mexico, England, Kuwait, Dubai, South Africa, Malaysia, Singapore, Bangladesh, Pakistan, Poland, Lithuania, the Slovak Republic, Ukraine, and Japan.  She has choreographed and performed Odissi dance in Telegu, Bengali, Malayalam, Tamil, Hindi, Urdu, Dogra, Kashmiri, as well as Sanskrit and Oriya for performances and festivals around the country and for Doordarshan and international television channels.  In Swarna Kamalam directed by K. Viswanath, Sharon was featured as herself to inspire the heroine to value her own Indian dance heritage.

 Sharon has received several awards and honors, including the Government of India's Acharya Narendra Dev Sarokar Samajic Samman presented by the Prime Minister of India in 1991, the Delhi Sahitya Kala Parishad's Parishad Samman '92 for her Outstanding Individual Contribution to Indian Arts, the Rashtiya Ekta Award of the All India National Unity Conference, Delhi Ratan, All India Conference of Intellectuals, Rajiv Gandhi Foundation, Bharat Nirman Award for \Role of Women in Nation Building\" in the field of Art and Dance

I started my training under Smt. Priti Patel and Smt. Sruti Banerjee in 1990. I specialise in all four aspects of classical Manipuri Dance i.e. Lai- Haraoba, Thang-Ta, Sankirtana and Rasleela. I received further training under the guidance of eminent Gurus Ojha Th. Babu Singh, Ojha Kh. Thorani Sabi Devi, Shri Lokendrajit Singh and Smt. Lakshmi Devi, senior artistes of Jawaharlal Nehru Manipur Dance Academy Imphal.

I am a graded artiste of Doordarshan and an empanelled artiste of ICCR. 
Along with my mentor I have performed in major dance festivals in India & abroad such as Khajuraho Festival, Uday Shankar Festival, and Festival of new Choreographies Delhi and in Bangladesh, Nepal, Poland and Germany.

Independently I have performed for the Dover Lane Festival, Uday Shankar Festival, Jaipur, Kolkata, Pune , Bangalore, Delhi,in the UK and Malaysia. I was also selected by Rotary International to perform & conduct workshops in Australia in 2004. I have successfully conducted workshops in Malaysia, Australia, Indonesia and the UK.

I was awarded The Shiromani Puraskar by Rotary International for her contribution towards dance and has received the uday Shankar award for the best talent of the year 2000, and was nominated by aprajita awards for young achievers 2012.

At present I work with hearing impaired children at the Oral School for the Deaf in Kolkata and at Kolkata Sanved I am training the dancers to be the future Dance Therapists.Dance/movement therapy, with its unique emphasis on nonverbal communication in assessment and treatment, is presented as an innovative therapeutic approach to address the comprehensive needs of these children and adolescents. The inclusion of dance/movement therapy as part of the interdisciplinary teaching in school addresses the psychosocial needs of the hearing impaired children.

I am also the secretary of World dance Alliance Kolkata Chapter.

Mahesh Mathai began his career as a director in advertising films and established a reputation as one of India's best talents. He was known for the iconic campaigns for Garden Vareli, Cadburys Dairy Milk chocolate (with the girl dancing on the cricket field), Gimme Red for Eveready Batteries,  Asain Paints with Pataudi and the Mumbai Indians launch with Hrithik Roshan, 

He founded Highlight Films which went on to become one of the most successful advertising commercials companies in India. His work for a range of clients including Unilever, Procter and Gamble, Coca Cola, Pepsi, Cadburys, Chevrolet, Eveready, McDowells, Philips, Asian Paints, Times of India, Seagrams, ICICI Bank and India Tourism covered nearly every possible brand category and won numerous Awards.


One of the pioneers of music video industry in the country, he partnered with Sony Music and BMG Records to launch the careers of singer Lucky Ali, and the band Bombay Vikings. The music video for Lucky Alis  O Sanam, shot at the pyramids became hugely popular.

In 2000 he made the feature film, Bhopal Express with Naseeruddin Shah, Kaykay and Vijay Raaz  (which launched the new composer trio of Ehsaan, Loy and Shankar) and opened the Panorama section of the prestigious Berlin Film Festival and won 7 International Awards.

In 2005 he completed a British film, Broken Thread starring Linus Roache (Batman Begins, Wings of a Dove, Hart's War, Chronicles of Riddick), Saffron Burrows (In the Name of the Father, Ganster Number One; Enigma; Troy; and Klimt.), Andrea Corr (The Commitments, Evita) and Roshan Seth (Gandhi, Monsoon Wedding).

In 2007 he founded the Blue Frog in Mumbai, the venue that became synonymous with live music, and is now branching out across the country.

In 2009 he drove an ambulance from London to Mongolia as part of a charity rally through 15 countries across Europe and Central Asia.

In 2011 he started working (with Anjum Rajabali) on the story of Rakesh Sharma, the first Indian to go to space.

Bhawsheel Sahni chose to rise over societal stereotypes and pursue what his soul wanted. I acted, portrayed a thousand characters under one maskthe mask of a thespian.
-As far as I can remember, I had always been involved in extra curricular activities since my school days. A keen participator in inter school level debates and quizzes, I loved performing at our annual day functions, which was a big headache for the school, and I, their pill (chuckles)
My schooling was from St. Johns High School and I am really fortunate to study in such a school where school life was way beyond studies. School life really plays a significant part in grooming a childs future and his personality. After completing my 10th, I did my 12th from Bhavan Vidyalaya School, Chandigarh, in the commerce stream. And the participation and the love for CCAs just increased.

I joined the Theatre For Theatre group, and that was it. My life really got on the right track and I knew what I wanted to do in my future. Even today when I am doing my Masters from Mumbai, my love for the films and acting is just growing beyond boundaries. Maybe there is something inside all of us that pushes us to perform greatly in our lives. And learning where my heart lies, was something which gave me the strength to chase my newly kindled drea

I joined a one month workshop25 days to be precise, which intrigued him, for he had for the first time been acquainted with the real side of dramatics. I left?Aaghaaz (college group) and joined my present theatre group in Chandigarh, Theatre For Theatre (TFT), and for the past 3 years has been associated with the same.
Now in Mumbai, I currently pursuing my Masters in Film, Television and Digital Video Production, from Xaviers Institute Of Communications. I aspires to carve a niche for Myself  in our very own Bollywood industry.

 Being specific, whenever I go for an audition, and I personally feel that the audition went extremely well and Ill be shortlisted, but when I do not get that call, I feel something might be lacking in me. I always take rejections and failures in my stride because to become successful, these have to become part and parcel of your lives.

Wow!oohhh..Bombay is fast man, pretty fast. Chandigarh is like that small beautiful blissful state, whereas Bombay can really teach you the meaning of survival. The people are so open minded and casual to talk to. On one street you find a helpful young lady, on the other you might run into an angry ignorant man. Both cities have their own charm. Its not like I miss Chandigarh very badly or something. I am actually starting to enjoy Mumbai and its whole vastness.

about_us:
The eternal romantic Karan, started his journey in the media industry as a model quickly reaching the top. His indelible charm and affable personality paved way for almost 250 successful Ad campaigns. From soaps to shoes to cooking oil; you name the product and he was the face of the brand. His popularity as a model got him a lot of offers from TV producers. Karan however, was always very picky about what he took up and decided to start his acting career with a drama series called Swabhimaan. It was an immensely popular TV series and Karan joined the cast as a young teenager essaying the role of Bobby. The series was written by the acclaimed author Shobha De and directed by Mahesh Bhatt. This was his stepping stone into the world of TV. He did a second show called Saaya on Sony TV that made him a household name and one of the popular actors on TV. His first love however, was always music. He continued singing jingles and at one point did the background music for a few serials he was a part of. 

Karan was trained as a musician at a very young age. He plays around 20 instruments and continues his education learning Hindustani classical vocals till date. A few more TV series followed, but the tug at his heart strings was too strong and he decided to take a sabbatical from TV despite being at the top of his game to pursue his first love; Music! Karan came up with the idea of starting Indias first boy band and reached out to a few people from the industry. Before he knew it, his dream took shape and some of the biggest names in the music industry joined hands to make it come true. A country wide band hunt of unprecedented magnitude was launched famously known as A Band of Boys. 5 boys were selected by a panel of eminent judges including the likes of Hari Haran and Lesle Lewis. The boys were selected, groomed and trained for 18 months in all aspects of being pop stars. They were unveiled in 2002 with their first single  Meri Neend Ud Gai Hai, released under the music label, Music Curry. The song was an unprecedented hit, smashed all records and went platinum in record time. 

The boys had arrived! Their next song, Tu he Mera Pyaar Gori went out to become an even bigger hit and the band became teen sensations. Video after video just kept adding to their growing popularity and firmly established them as the top brand in the Indie Music Scene. Owing to their immense popularity, a semi autobiographical mainstream movie called Kis Kis Ko followed which was produced by Medient Entertainment (which Karan was a part of) and released by Eros International. Various albums like Nain Katari, Aa Bhi Jaa etc. released by Universal Worldwide and T Series made them a household name. The Band continued their journey on various stages around the world with their live wire on stage performances during almost 800 shows across the globe. 

Having the ability to multitask, Karan was not only performing as an artist but was also producing music videos for his own band, for others and also doing TV commercials by the name of his production company called Crooner Studios. He also turned a TV producer, producing a show for Zee TV called, Zindagi Badal Sakta Hai Haadsa for Zee TV  A first of its kind storytelling daily thriller. He hosted the very popular Zee Antakshari after the departure of Anu Kapoor as a host and also played the lead character in the path breaking series called Jassi Jaisi Koi Nahin as Jassis love interest. 

He also ventured into solo stage performances and his interactive performances coupled with a unique on stage story telling aspect are a big favourite with the audiences. He continues doing solo shows and performing with the Band of Boys. Karan has finally released his single Challa on the digital platform through Eros Now. It hit 100,000 views in just a few days, which was quite uncharacteristic for an Indie album with purely organic growth. A full fledged Indie Pop Album is on the anvil. 

Karan loves wearing multiple hats. Presently he is gearing up for his Hindi Album, producing content, is a creative consultant to a few companies, is creating new IPs as an entrepreneur, setting up his film production house and writing films. He is a non conformist who follows his heart and dreams. He is a heretic and not afflicted by any dogmas. He believes in living life one moment at a time adding value to whatever and whoevers life he touches. 

He is a poet, philosopher, writer, artist, businessman, entrepreneur, philanthropist and incurable romantic.

I was born in a Parsee family on October 23, 1973. My family runs a poultry farm. My name means 'Fairy's daughter'.
I made My first appearance as a model for Clearisil, & a music video titled 'Nahin Raktha Dil Mein Kuch', then I re-located to New York, in the United States of America to study and obtain a degree in MBA. While there, I took part in theatrical plays with Lee Strasberg.

After obtaining My MBA I returned home to assist My dad at their poultry farm, and also appeared in a TV play called 'Hum Pardesi Ho Gaye', where I played the character of a woman named Maya.

'Bollywood Calling' was My debut on the tinsel screen during the year 2001, thereafter this attractive young Parsi went on to act in 11 more movies, including the Hollywood flick 'Exitz' where I portrays the character of an Indian model. I has also acted the role of former Indian Prime Minister Indira Gandhi in a Chinese movie 'Bandung Sonata'.

On December 9, 2006 I got married to Boman Rustom Irani, who is a Board Director of Rustomjee Builders. She continues to accept offers and appears in movies.

I have been in photography since 1996. Based in Hyderabad I work in Fashion, Advertising & Commercial Photography. I hold a  Fashion & Advertising Diploma in photography and have experience in Cinematography for regional and national language. 

I have a very unique style that is cinematic with underlying narratives. I own studio space in Jubilee Hills to cater my creative ideology and digital post processing. Travelling is one of my passions and I have worked in different parts of India and Abroad.

I use state-of-the art photographic equipment and have developed the techniques and systems to offer high-quality professional results. I have also specialized in aerial Photography and I am better suited for catalogue and E commerce photography.

I have worked for Ramoji Film City, J K Hydro Power,  Srivalli Shipping, Fly Tech Aviation, Apollo Health Care, BVRIT, Weavers India, UNV fashions, Yash E Bike and various other Film Advertising

I had a liberal and encouraging familial upbringing, which was coupled with an intensive period of study under the illustrious tabla maestro Nikhil Ghosh. I training with this veritable repository of traditional compositions from the Delhi, Ajrada, Lucknow, Farukhabad and Punjab schools of tabla playing enabled  to widen his horizons.
My today regarded as an accomplished soloist and a perfect foil to vocal and instrumental music or dance recitals. I has remains a keen student of music, despite the acclaim I has received over the years from cognoscenti and general public and by way of awards like the scholarship for advanced training in tabla instituted by the Government of India and the Aditya Birla Kala Kiran Award.
I participation in Indian music recitals and in cross-cultural musical collaborations have taken me on extensive tours within India and overseas. My first solo album distributed by Underscore Records reaches listeners among a host of others, which feature me as accompanist on national and international record labels. Broadcasting and television networks have also recorded.
I spent fruitful years as artist-in-residence at the University of New England, Australia, and as guest lecturer at the Music Department, University of Mumbai, and several other universities in other countries. I has put to use the experience I gained as teacher in the many lecture-demonstrations and workshops that I has conducted.
I has continues to enrich my musical persona in my capacity as composer to film, theatre and dance projects. I has won the Natyadarpan Best Background Score Award for 1998, for my music to the Marathi play Tumbara directed by Sunil Shanbag.
Endeavouring to understand my position in a historical continuum, I realised the symbiotic relationship between performance and research. I has therefore continues to be a keen student of History, an area in which i was awarded a doctorate.

I am Subbulakshmi Hariharan, a veteran violinist in the Carnatic style. I have been trained in music from Swati Tirunal College of Music, Trivandrum from where I have completed 8 years course in violin(Carnatic style). I have also achieved the honour of Gana Bhushana and Gana Praveena. After completing my studies, I had the privilege to be trained in music from Chembai Memorial Govt. Music College , Palakkad (Kerala) in violin. 

I offer training to the students in violin at Shivanjali Trust, Coimbatore and has produced good violinist from the Trust. 

I am highly experienced in Carnatic violin and a member of the great generations that truly stick on to the rich tradition of Carnatic music without polluting it with later additions. Hence I represent a real heritage of age old Guruparampara. I have been offering my services as a senior Professor in Violin at Government Music College , Coimbatore for 10 years in their music department. I later shifted to Jamshedpur after my marriage in the year 2004. I have a rich experience in both Carnatic Kutchery and dance programmes through my calibre.

My Hobbies are Playing Violin, Reading Books, Magazines, Cooking and Listening to Carnatic Music.

I Participated as a Judge in many Music Compitition organised in Tamil Nadu and attended Refresher Course in Music conducted by Art and cultural Department, Government of Tamil Nadu at Chennai and acted as Examination head of Music under Tamil Nadu Government Music College and Coimbatore.

I have accompanied on violin with Carnatic Maestro and renowned music director of Asianet Television, Thiruvananthapuram for his concert at Kerala Samajam School and Jamshedpur during the 60th year of the school recently. I had also accompained on violin with 1st non residential indian lady carnatic vocal singer from Singapore miss Sushma Somasekharan during diamond Jubilee celebration of the Rasika Ranjan Sabha at Kolkata.

It is said that melody & rhythm is a rare & uncommon combination. Pt. Anant Terdal is renowned name in the field of Hindustani Classical music. Born in a family of musicians at Belgaum in 1941, Panditji was fascinated by the Hindustani Classical Music at a tender age of seven. Then onwards he has dedicated himself to the cause of Hindustani Classical Music and achieved great heights in that field.

He received his preliminary training in music from his uncle Shri. Keshavacharya and his mother Smt. Bhagirathi. Thereafter, he came under the tutelage of Shri.Baburao Borkar, a talented Harmonium player who had a considerable impact upon him. At the same time he had a privilege of learning vocal music from Dr.G.D.Joshi, (Sangeet Praveen) of Gwalior Gharana. Then, he learnt the nuances of Kirana Gharana from late Pt.R.N.Joshi buwa. In 1959 he got the title of Sangeet Visharad from Akhil Bharateeya Gandharva Mahavidyalay. In 1983, Pt. Terdal became the Ganda Bandh disciple of Pt. Bhimsen Joshi  the doyen of Kirana Gharana. Since then he has been imbibing the depths of Hindustani Classical Music from the maestro. 

Pt. Terdals singing is characterized by the clarity of swaras in three octaves, thoughtful and bhava poorna rendition of ragas in both vilambit and drut layas. Along with the classical music, he is eloquent in presenting Marathi Natyageet, Bhajans, Kannada Devarnamas etc.


Pt. Terdal has travelled extensively within India on his musical performances under the aegis of various organizations including the prestigious Sawai Gandharva festival of Pune, Akhil Bharateeya Gandharva Mahavidyalay, Karnataka Sangeet and Nrutya Academy, Ramkrishna Sangeet Sammelan organised by the Maharashtra Lalit Kala Nidhi, Mumbai, Tansen Sangeet Sammelan - Kolkata, Sangeet Research Academy of Kolkata, Master Deenanath Mangeshkar Smruti Sangeet Sammelan -Goa etc and performed along with the stalwarts of the Indian classical music including Pt.Shivkumar Sharma, Pt.C.R.Vyas, Pt.Hariprasad Chourasia, Ustad Zakir Hussain, late Ustad Bismillah Khan, Ustad Hafiz Ahmed Khan, Smt.Sunanda Patnaik, late Pt.Jitendra Abhisheki, Pt.Swapan Choudhari etc. His performances have been acclaimed by the musicians, music critics and media alike. Recently he toured Middle-east on his musical performances organized by Maharashtra Mandal and Kannada Sangh.

Pt. Terdal has been performing on All India Radio since 1975. In 1981 his National Progrmme of music was broadcast. His programmes have also been telecast by Doordarshan and other private channels from various centres including Mumbai, Goa and Bangalore.

Various titles have come his way recognizing his genius in Hidustani Classical music. He was given the title of Sur Mani by Sur Singar Sansad. In 2001 he was honoured with the title of Kalashri by the Karnataka State Sangeet Academy. 

Pt. Terdals music is also available on cassettes and CDs. Anand Audio Cassette Company of Bangalore has released the cassettes of his devotional songs. Ganapati Bhat Music Academy, Hasanagi, has released a CD of Pt.Terdals classical music.

I am Anjana Jha  I started learning the nuances of Kathak under the guidance of Guru Shri Sukh Dev Singh Kushwah at a tender age of 8.

Later I was admitted in the prestigious Kathak Kendra, National Institute of Kathak Dance, New Delhi, where i received scholarship for five consecutive years from the Ministry of Culture in India. I started advanced training in Kathak under the guidance of world-renowned Kathak Maestro Pt. Rajendra Gangani of the Jaipur Gharana. I imbibed the best from my guru and blossomed into an artist of fine calibre.

After receiving a Post Graduate Diploma in Kathak Dance with Honours I furthered my studies and received a PhD in Kathak Dance from Indra Kala Sangeet Vishwavidyalaya, Khairagarh University in Chhattisgarh, India. During my doctorate studies I also served as an examiner in the University Examination Board.

My style of artistic expression is characterised by subtle abhinaya, fast and clear footwork and spins, clear movements, grace and flawless beauty of Kathak dance. My solo performances fill the atmosphere with grace and i expressions and gestures create an emotion of great beauty, purity and sublimity in the audience. I  approach to dance is to fully embody the beauty of rhythm and grace in Kathak classical dance. My skills of Kathak language are exceptional and have a touch of perfection.   These are some of the fine hallmarks of my Kathak performance and have established me as a dedicated professional artist with national and international exposure.

As a solo and leading group Kathak dancer and choreographer, I have performed on many prestigious platforms in India, Australia, Singapore, Switzerland, Malaysia, Dubai, Qatar, Doha, Bahrain, Oman, Muscat, Kuwait, Iceland, Norway, and Thailand.  This has gained my international recognition as a renowned Kathak dancer and choreographer.

I was the first Kathak teacher and performer in the history of Thailand, through the Indian Cultural Center of Indian Embassy in Bangkok and was an empanelled artist with the Indian Council for Cultural Relations (ICCR) reference panel of artists.

In 2005, I represented India as a Kathak dancer during the Tour to Iceland led by the President of India, Honourable A.P.J Abdul Kalam.

I am  A-Graded Artist of the Delhi Doordarshan national TV channel in India with my programs telecast in Delhi, Gwalior, and Kerala.

My repertoire includes performances of Kathak dance in Hindustani Classical Music as well as in Carnatic Classical Music. I has also worked with renowned South Indian actors and actresses and musicians. In addition to my outstanding Kathak performance, my excels in classical and semi-classical vocal music, Hindustani musical instrument pakhawaj, and yoga.

Today with complete devotion and dedication she performs worldwide and imparts my knowledge to the next generation.

Currently I am working as a Associate Professor (Head of Dance Department) at Raja Mansingh Tomar Music & Arts University in Gwalior.

Magicians Aladin and The Lady are well-established magicians in the South Indian state of Kerala. Based out of Cochin (Kochi), they have earned the undeniable reputation of being the leading entertainers for corporate as well as personal events.  

Already, Aladin and The Lady has carved a niche among the magicians in Cochin. Popular on leading TV channels and corporate events on account of the unique tricks and performance, Aladin and team

What sets us apart from other magicians in Kerala or for that matter magicians in India is that we add a lot of humour and comedy, which make the entire show more interesting and appealing to a wider audience. In fact, this eclectic blend of comedy and an assortment of original magic tricks have endeared us to the masses not only in Kochi but all over Kerala. The fact that we have been featured many times in the leading newspapers in Kerala is a testament to the wide popularity and acceptance enjoyed by Aladin and team.

Aladins tricks are very original and his presentation comic. He ensures the active participation of audience in all his shows. This interactivity makes the show all the more entertaining as the audience gets a first-hand chance to experiment with various tricks on offer.

Another inimitable aspect about Aladin is his ability to perform the wonderful act of ventriloquism, an art better described as an illusion of sound, in 1998. Already, Aladins ventriloquism techniques have gained wide appreciation through his shows in Kochu TV, a kids TV channel in Kerala.

We introduced 'Aladin Comadin'  a magic show blended with comedy in 2002.

about_us:
Satheesh Kumar, born and brought up in a middle class agricultural family in a small village situated in one of the breezy, tranquil geographical locations in Kerala, India. A silent observer, admirer of the serene nature and its heavenly beauty. An academic professional education in Law was not able to stop me from the unavoidable call and strong hold for natures art, painting with light.

Done Mass Communication and Still Photography. Started framing and freezing nature and its creations. The sense of aesthetics got naturally. Worked for some photo stock agencies.  Earlier, worked with some ad agencies as a copywriter trainee and a client servicing executive.

Took photography as a profession by special ordain. It is really Gods gift. Parents gave the support. Prof. Nantu showed the way. Got training from Mr. Vipin Das, renowned cinematographer-film maker and from Mr. Sivan, renowned photographer-film maker. Worked with Sanjay Ramachandran,. Vinod,. Pankaj Shah and. Manmohan Singh Arora. All are pioneers, talented and experts in painting with light in their own area of specialisation.  All of them shared their knowledge and experience about the art and craft of Photography.

My professional exposure in major cities like Dubai, Bangalore, Mumbai, Delhi, Kochi, Trivandrum and Coimbatore gave me a new and acute outlook. Bored of closed employer environments where creativity cannot be fully utilized, I came out.

Now, working as a freelance photographer in India capturing Automotive, Architecture, Food, Interior, Industrial, Products, Nature, Travel and, and more

I am interested to travel and shoot extensively, not just conventional pictures but . classics!

I am not just a Sound recordist, but a Camera assistant and Mister Fix-it. 
I will organize and make the impossible possible.

Shoots in Asia can be stressfull. I have worked with many european crews and production houses.

For shoots I have traveld in every corner of southeast asia, to europe and to the former sowjet union.

I learned my job from several german cameraman, who had been posted in Delhi.

Since then I have worked on many long form televison productions mostly for Swiss, Austrian and German TV.

I started at one of Delhis Light and equipment rental houses. That is why I understand lighting for TV and film very well and assist when ever I can.

Besides TV, I have worked on Productions for government bodies, NGO's, Foundations and on corporate films.

I love my work especially when it involves travel.

Sarvani Yadavalli, an epitome of dance coupled with strong fortitude and talent, is an avid Indian Classical dancer. An engineer by profession, Sarvani is highly passionate about dance.  With more than two decades of performing experience in more than ten countries, Sarvani staged shows in different national and international events. She has toured South, South East Asia & UK performing and conducting workshops propagating the rich Indian cultural heritage. Her choreographies enthrall the audience transporting them to another world. Dance exponents and media have time and again commended her as one of the best dancers of her generation. She was honoured with the national Nrithya Shiromani award by Utkal Yuva Sanskrutik Sangh, with the titles Nrithya Vilasini & Nrithya Bharathi and many more.  She is an empanelled artist in Indian Council for Cultural Relations (ICCR) and India World Cultural Forum (IWCF).

Her passion for excellence is evident in every walk of her life. A state topper in her college in the state of Andhra Pradesh, she did her engineering from one of the most prestigious colleges of India Birla Institute of Technology and Science (BITS, Pilani). Her active involvement in several departments and clubs enabled her to develop into a well-rounded individual with an exposure to various facets of life.  She is the recipient of many prestigious awards such as Monalidey day award, Pratibha award, Best paper award, BITSAA 30 under 30 awards given to the alumni of Bits, Pilani with significant achievement in their field. She balances her work life and dance carrier & carries forward her enthusiasm for academics and arts with the tremendous support of her family members.

Using the Indian classical dance form, Sarvani proposes to take up several social issues and address them in her attempt to perpetuate peace and harmony. She started Sahasra Fine Arts and intends to train many others in this beautiful art form.

My tryst with clay started 17 years ago and I first walked the \'potter\'s path\' holding the hand of a traditional potter in India. From there, I went on to develop my initial skills and aesthetics at the Delhi Blue Pottery, and then advanced ceramics at the private studio of Dipalee and PR Daroz. I am a Fullbright Scholar and received my Master of Arts from the University of Dallas (Texas, USA) in 2008. This experience under Dan Hammett had immense influence in Rahul\'s approach and expression. I have several shows to my credit, including solo shows at the William Blakeley Gallery at University of Dallas (USA), Cymroza Art Gallery in Mumbai, Gallery Threshold and The American Centre in Delhi; and participation in several group shows including Feats of Clay, Golden Earth, Journey through Clay, Harmony and the Mad Hatter\'s Tea Party to name a select few. I delivered a presentation on contemporary Indian ceramics at the Pittsburgh (USA) conference of National Council on Education for the Ceramic Arts (NCECA) in 2008. I regularly contributes to national dailies and ceramic magazines. I am a three time national AIFACS awardee. Most of my works are vessels, though they express some of the most abstract thoughts on opposing energies and duality of life. I enjoys working with varied scale; my work ranges from 3 feet to 1 inch in height. I teach advanced ceramics at my personal studio in Gurgaon (India) finding out time from my busy schedule as a corporate executive in the field of business research.

I am an an Indian film actor, appeared in six different Indian regional film industry Career.

I began my acting career by appearing in television serials including Antariksh and Mayavi, which was first 3D serial in Tamil television. I made my film début with The Angrez (2006), an experimental crossover film shot in Hyderabadi Urdu . Subsequently, I made my début in Tamil cinema with Radha Mohan's family drama, Abhiyum Naanum (2008). I successfully auditioned for the role in Mumbai, by turning up dressed as the Sikh character in the film, prompting the makers to believe that  actually was a Punjabi. Portraying as Trisha's Punjabi fiancé, my role received critical acclaim and the film performed well at the box office. After working with Prakash Raj in the second film, I got several further offers to appear in supporting roles in films starring veteran actors.I appeared as a police officer, working alongside Kamal Haasan, Mohanlal and Venkatesh in the bilingual film Unnaipol Oruvan (2009, while I then portrayed an army general in Major Ravi's war film Kandahar, where I appeared with Mohanlal and Amitabh Bachchan. I also shot and completed a thriller film titled Muriyadi with Sathyaraj by Selva, but the film failed to have a theatrical release owing to Kavithalayaa Productions' financial troubles. During the period, I also opted out of another multi-starrer Mankatha (2011), and instead chose to work on another bilingual Tamil and Hindi film, Panithuli , in a solo lead role. Shot entirely in the USA, the film opened to negative reviews and performed poorly at the box office. Furthermore, I appeared with another veteran actor, Nagarjuna, during the making of Damarukam (2012), which became my first straight Telugu film.

I worked on three projects in 2013, prioritising my work on Tamil cinema. I appeared in Sundar C's bilingual film, Theeya Velai Seiyyanum Kumaru in a supporting role of an office worker, while I was seen as a police officer in the action film, Ivan Veramathiri. I also portrayed the role of a prince in Roopa Iyer's Kannada and Tamil bilingual film, Chandra, and revealed that I signed on after hearing that Shriya Saran would be portraying the lead role. During the same year, I also portrayed a supporting role in Mohan Raja's Thani Oruvan, which went on to become a blockbuster at the box office.

Hello Friends.. I am Rajan srivastava, and I have done my studies in Kanpur, Uttar Pradesh.  My target was just to make people laugh. When I was in Kanpur at that time I was a struggler and no one knows me. But I want to be a mimicrian & comedian. In 2005 I have started anchoring in ETV Uttar Pradesh in Lucknow and the show Lage Rahiye.

  When I left Lage Rahiye I started comedy for Zee Smile, the show name is Kyuki ye hai hasya Mukabla this was the show where I reached semi finals. Just because of that two comedy shows people knew me as a comedian Rajan Srivastav, and at that time I was very busy in stage shows in all over India.

I am an Action Director, who has done many Bollywood Indian Motion Pictures. Born in Orissa, I completed my education there and eventually settled down in Mumbai. The inception of my career began in 1990 as a Stunt man - a man with dreams and ambition. My hard work, passion and persistence paid off and within no time he was promoted to the designation of Assistant Fight Master in which I did numerous Bollywood films. 

In the initial days of my career I worked as an Assistant to successful, popular and veteran Action Director Veeru Devgan for the films -- Phool Aur Kaante, Jigar, Dilwaale, Vishwaatma, Ishq etc. Later I assisted Alan Amin in Mission Kashmir, The Legends of Bhagat Singh, Qayamat, Hero etc. During this period I also performed dare-devil stunts as a duplicate of Ajay Devgn, Amitabh Bachchan, Anil Kapoor, Shahrukh Khan, Salman Khan, Suniel Shetty, Abhishek Bachchan, Sanjay Dutt, Sunny Deol and Akshay Kumar. 

 Aneez Bazmee gave me my first break as an independent Action Director in the film -- No Entry, followed by Inder Kumar signing me for the film Masti. My work was highly appreciated and I instantly got the deserving recognition in the industry. 

Since 2004 -- the year I became an Action Director till 2010,  I have done over 60 films which includes Karam, Virrudh, Dhamaal, Pyaare Mohan, Teesri Aankh, The Stoneman Murders, Go, Ashique Banaaya Aapne, City of Gold, Mi Shivaji Raje Bhosle Boltoy, Dedh Ishqiya and many more.

I have also done Hollywood films - American Daylight with Director Roger Christian, Sacred Evil and The Saint Who Thought Otherwise. 

I also participated in 'World Stunt Show' -- an international stunt competition in the year 2003 which was held in Moscow. 
 
Apart from feature films, I have done many Ad-films which includes Britania's 'Hide and Seek' with Hrithik Roshan and Esha Sherwani, and 'Smart Chips' with Aamir Khan. 

As an Action Director I have professional affiliation with reputed and big production houses like Mahesh Manjrekar Productions, Kaliedoscope, Boney Kapoor's S.K. Films, Maruti International, Baweja Films, Ram Gopal Verma Productions and others.

Growing up surrounded by both Hindustani and Western music, Zoheb Ahmed eventually found his way into the Indian film and advertising industry as a Music Director. For the past six years, Zoheb has crafted countless advertising jingles, background scores and full songs, which have earned him a reputation in Bollywood as a brilliant, disciplined and a professional composer. His feature scores can be found in Sharat Katariyas 10ml Love, a 2012 Hindi comedy adaptation of Shakespeares A Midsummer Nights Dream, Hollywood film Breakdown, Background Score for The Perfect Girl and many more.

Before turning to music direction and production, Zoheb made his name as a talented singer, first noticed in 2003 when he won the intercollegiate special competition of Sa Re Ga Ma Pa, Indias version of American Idol. Zohebs success as a vocalist led him to travel the world for several years as the lead singer of Bharati, an international stage production that features Indian culture through music. Zoheb had performed with many international artists such as Lionel Richie, Quincy Jones, Kanye West for Mawazine festival Morocco in 2010.

Zoheb gained his musical education in his hometown city of Bhilai, where he learned Western music and Indian semi classical under his father, Mr. Iqbal Ahmed. Zoheb later studied Hindustani classical music in Mumbai under the renowned Ustad Ghulam Mustafa Khan. Zohebs keen understanding of both Western and Indian tonality made him a perfect collaborator for Independent Music. Zoheb says that every project is a journey to find the roots of different genres and cultures through music and to discover the traditional and spiritual values held within them.

about_us:
Hello, This is Asavari Pawar, an Indian Classical Dancer.
I inherited a love for this classical art from my illustrious father, Padmashri Guru Pratap Pawar, who is regarded one of the leading exponents of the Lucknow gharana of Kathak. 
I took to dancing from the age of 8 as part of my fathers dance troupe, Triveni in London, and have never looked back since.

While pursuing my education in London (I obtained A Levels in English and French from St. Anns Convent in Ealing), I continued to blossom into a dancer of immense promise. 
My production, The Coat (portraying the turmoil of emotions faced by a village girl about to leave for Britain to meet her husband there), won the first Prime Minister John Majors Award in 1991. 
Since then, The Coat has been reproduced over 35 times in several countries.

I returned to India and underwent three years of rigorous training with Pt. Vijay Shankar and perfected the art of the Kathak dance form, assimilating its layakari (rhythm) aspects. 
I also took training in classical singing under the renowned Smt. Girija Devi. 
Apart from Kathak I have trained Ballet and African Folk with Haitian Ballerina Madame Lavinia Williams. 

Endowed with a lissome figure and inherent grace, I suffuse my recitals with a rare lyricism.

I am a camera nomad.
German by upbringing, German by education - diplomas and masters, German when it comes to punctuality.
But then I am a citizen of this world now.
I am multilingual - firm in two and familiar to the sounds of three more.
Last year I have been shooting in 14 countries.
I am a fan of vietnamese and thai food.
I fly 30sqm of fabric 3000 meters off nepali soil whenever I find the time to go and I have a long history of dangling from ropes or jamming my fingers into tiny cracks of a mountains wall.
I am learning to dive and and had my first underwater shoot last year for swiss television in Tanzania.
I have driven nearly 190000 km of hindustani roads on many different Enfield\'s.
I have had masterclasses with leading cinematographers, some of those where held in the middle of the night and under the influence of the finest european beers.
I have, as you can see in my portfolio, a great deal of international awards, but someone else is dusting them off every week, because they don\'t fit in my suitcase.
Reportage and documentary camera is my strong suit - or like my film school professor called it \\the ultimate dance with life itself.\\"

Timelapse and Hyperlapse fascinate me.
I love a challenge. So call me for your next project."

German by upbringing, German by education - diplomas and masters, German when it comes to punctuality.
But then I am a citizen of this world now.
I am multilingual - firm in two and familiar to the sounds of three more.
Last year I have been shooting in 14 countries.
I am a fan of vietnamese and thai food.
I fly 30sqm of fabric 3000 meters off nepali soil whenever I find the time to go and I have a long history of dangling from ropes or jamming my fingers into tiny cracks of a mountains wall.
I am learning to dive and and had my first underwater shoot last year for swiss television in Tanzania.
I have driven nearly 190000 km of hindustani roads on many different Enfield\'s.
I have had masterclasses with leading cinematographers, some of those where held in the middle of the night and under the influence of the finest european beers.
I have, as you can see in my portfolio, a great deal of international awards, but someone else is dusting them off every week, because they don\'t fit in my suitcase.
Reportage and documentary camera is my strong suit - or like my film school professor called it \\the ultimate dance with life itself.\\"

Timelapse and Hyperlapse fascinate me.
I love a challenge. So call me for your next project."

Im a freelance Sound Recordist/ Production Sound Mixer and Sound Designer with many years of professional experience on a wide variety of projects and an extensive knowledge of workflows in all areas of production sound and sound design - film, commercial, documentary, music, corporate and TV.

Ive worked alongside A-list directors/producers such as Danny Boyle, Ang Lee, John Madden, Angelina Jolie, Mira Nair, Dede Gardner, Charles Schlissel and actors such as Judy Dench, Bill Nighy, Maggie Smith, Celia Imrie, Julia Roberts, Ashton Kutcher, Dev Patel, Harvey Keitel, Shah Rukh Khan, Rajinikanth and Irrfan Khan to name a few.

Some of the feature films for which I have recorded sync sound are  First They Killed My Father, Jobs, The Reluctant Fundamentalist, Mission Impossible (Ghost Protocol), Raabta and Highway.

I studied sound at the national film school - Film and Television Institute of India, Pune.
Here, I had the opportunity to watch cinema from across the world, learn the ropes of filmmaking, understand the importance of sound in film, explore its various possibilities and imbibe its many technical and aesthetic aspects.

Being associated with sound mixers such as Resul Pookutty and Drew Kunin during my initial years of work, gave me the opportunity to be on notable films like Slumdog Millionare, The Best Exotic Marigold Hotel, Life of Pi and Eat Pray Love, which enriched me tremendously, set my standards very high and helped me imbibe the technical proficiency and work ethic of the Hollywood system.

I\'m currently based in India and Europe and available for projects locally and internationally.

A diploma in fashion designing and an extensive experience of designing clothes for well known personalities since 1997, Sima Mehta brings the best for you through her collection. Hi, I am Shailesh Ranjak , i am a Dancer and the Coreographer based in Mumbai and I am the Owner Of SDFA

Headquartered at the heart of entertainment in the country, Mumbai, Star Dance and Fitness Academy (SDFA) is one of the few registered dance academies of the city.

It blends a heady mix of styles in its teachings - including Jazz, Freestyle, Hip-Hop, Bolly Salsa, Contemporary and many more genres. Established in 2008, SDFA operates from 21 centres across the city, catering to over 1500 students.

SDFA takes pride in its association with Mumbai Police and numerous NGO\'s across Mumbai imparting free dance training to its deserving students and offering them a professional platform to perform. Star Nite is the annual show of the Academy where talents from a cross section of society merge to perform to packed audiences. The Tukaram Ombale Rolling Trophy and the Inter Centre Dance Championship are the highlights of the evening each year. Numerous bollywood celebrities and personalities from different walks of life have endorsed this brand with their presence at Star Nite over the years.

Tie ups with numerous prestigious educational institutions of Mumbai, imparting dance education, Corporate Launches, Ad Films, Sangeet Sandhyas are some of the arenas the academy focuses on.

about_us:
Jamshid is a Film Professional with a decade of experience in the industry. He has worked on various projects including mainstream hindi , regional and International feature films in various capacities apart from a large number of TVC's, AV's, Corporate Films and Web Series. An MBA in Communications, he started out as a Media Planner before his heart pulled him into the field he loved most and wanted to be part of.

 With a sound knowledge in the Production and Technical aspects of film making, he has taken a step towards finally fulfilling his dream and raison d'etre, Direction, by making his short feature, Akuri...and a pinch of hope!!

Tushar Bhatt is a Kathak dancer and disciple of Guru Sri Dharamshibhai shah Bhavnagar, Gujarat. Graduate in Kathak from the University Akhil Bharatiya Gandharva Maha Vidhyalay Mandal-Mumbai. Auditioned artist from Bangalore doordarshan. Have performed in India and abroad .
Performances Abroad:
52nd Republic Day Celebrations in Bern and Geneva Switzerland
Cultural Exchange programmed for Indian Council for Cultural Relations (ICCR), in South Africa - Lusaka. Zambia - Tanzania and Re- Union Islands
ICCR Cultural Exchange Programme in Bali, Indonesia, Malaysia , U.K.
Asian Countries, Gulf Countries and U.S.A and Candad

Delhi based Shoots and Shoots Photography is specialised in cinematic wedding filmsand candid photography. We are working with some of the most innovative wedding beauty,event, fashion, glamour, product, industrial, edvertising, interior & exterior photographers with a different approach towards archiving your precious moments. The magical look of cinema and the art of story telling is what will make you remember the most throughout your life.

We are famous for our celebrities amongst others: Peenaz Masani, Harbhajan Maan, Shahrukh Khan, Amrita Rao, Hrithik Roshan, Sonam Kapoor, Aryan Ved, Praveen Kumar (bhim) and Yana Gupta. Apart from celebrities our major clients include Atlas Cycles, Kamdhenu, Bajaj Motors, Indo, Goodrich Agrochem, Leh Berry, Bagga Jewellers, Sycorian, Realistic Realtors, Pookei, St. Joseph\'s School, Chhabra555, Modelama, Insta,charming, Roop Jewellers, Bonton, Solluna Resort, Quality Innhimdev, Oriant Craft, Omaxe, Shahi Export House,Sonalika Tractors, Max Hospital and many more.

Started back in 1990 as a small level photo studio at Janakpuri, we have tried to emerge as a picture which delivers moments in a unique flavour to make them feel like yesterday. Every member of our team is devoted to give you candid and narrative moments which weave a story around your special moments.

Me, Shyam Prasad, I personally entered this industry in 1990, taking up this field as a new challenge, since then I am about to converge an end product which has the best of all: in image capturing, in presentation and the best in cinematography as well.

Tulip Joshi was launched by Yash Chopra in his 2004 hit 'Mere Yaar ki Shaadi Hai'. Since then she has surprised one and all by growing from strength to strength.

In her brief acting career she has worked with the biggest stars and the biggest banners (Yash Chopra, Ashtavinayak, Mahesh Bhatt, Shaahid Kapoor, Pawan Kalyan, Mamoothy, Upendra, Harbhajan Mann to name a few).

While her beauty is indisputable, she has made a mark for herself with power packed performances that have forced even the worst critics to applaud her talent (Mathrabhoomi was rated as one of the ten best films of the world by Time Magazine while her suicide bomber role in Dhokha made a nation wake up.)

A visit to her home will show you an entire wall stacked with a variety of awards ranging from sports, athletics to National awards for Acting to International performance awards.

Having consciously chosen to stay away from the rat race, Tulip has stuck to one film a year and has always been far away from scandals, affairs and other negative publicity common to her industry

A visit to her home will show you an entire wall stacked with a variety of awards ranging from sports, athletics to National awards for Acting to International performance awards.

Having consciously chosen to stay away from the rat race, Tulip has stuck to one film a year and has always been far away from scandals, affairs and other negative publicity common to her industry

I started my career in the year 1985 & opened my own Academy of
Fashion & Dance under the name of PAMS ACADEMY.I have performed in various cities in India along with my troupe. I also had the
opportunity to perform in Greece,Frankfurt,Heidleburg,Dubai & Abu
Dhabi.


I have also been choreographing Sangeet Functions for elite Weddings
like the Goenkas ,Jajoos,Agrawals, Goyal ,Rao, etc. I have assisted
in Hindi Feature films & have also done projects for- Platform, Aaja
Sanam,Raja Hindustani,Dhadkan to name a few. I have independently
choreographed in Aatank Hi Aatank.

The most talked about dance show Nach Baliye 3, had me training &
choreographing Sweta Keswani & Alexx ONell & I was successful in
bringing them to the top 4 category.

I am the recipient of the Lions Gold Awards 2007 for being the
most favourite choreographer on television. I have also been honoured to
have judged various live Fashion & dance competitions like
Malhar, Ghungroos, Syncytium and many Inter-collegiate dance competitions till date.

I conduct workshops in Bollywood Dancing & Indian
Fashions for tourists from all over the world.

Sachin\'s first film in 1996-1997 as Line Producer for ZDF was an incredible journey, filming the Ganga from source at Gaumukh, to its merging into the Bay of Bengal. \\River of Laughter River of Tears\\" (Dir. Jens Monath

about_us: As the Mansarovar lake echoes divine scintillations that pacifies the human soul and the waves sing a divine music that lifts and transcends ones consciousness music also takes us to eternity, the realm of divine. One can feel the same ecstasy when he/she practices the subtle notes of Indian classical music. Twin sisters Abha & Vibha Chaurasia have brought few drops of this divine nectar after practicing Indian classical music right from their childhood. Their father Shri Ramnarayan Chaurasia and mother Smt. Madhubala Chaurasia inspired, supported and encouraged them, taught them to pursue the most subtle aspects of classical music. Traversing in the vast ocean of Indian Classical Music Abha & Vibha have dedicated their life and soul to music. They sing from their heart so as to take the listener to the realm of eternal bliss, in toto, they rightly say that the sole motto of their singing is to elevate their own consciousness and to uplift the consciousness of their audiences. \\Abha & Vibha
profile_color: the singers of Gwalior Gharana are the only female vocalists in Northern Indian Classical Music who sing Jugalbandi (duet).\\""
