about_us:
Before becoming Indias first hip-hop dance crew, RnG was just an ordinary bunch of extraordinary dancers. Their energy and charisma captured the attention of audiences in Boogie Woogie. Rohan Rokade, the founder, gathered the best dancers from Nallasopara (a suburb of Mumbai) who are now known as Rohan N Group. Boogie Woogie proved to be an opening platform for them. This is where RnG was entitled as Indias first hip-hop dance crew. They have worked as a team since then. 

Rohan Rokade has been a part of the industry since 15 years and has been to US for concerts. During his visit there, he saw street dancers doing hip-hop and b-boying and thats when he decided to introduce that style of dance in India. With confidence at its peak and flexibility skills, they entertained their way into the homes and hearts of people during Indias Got Talent. Their flawless & impacting performances have been creating a sensation till date, which in turn got them the opportunities to do dozens of stage performances, concerts, reality shows and movies. RnG has motivated many dancers & crews to achieve their unfulfilled dreams by being an inspiration. 

RnG is a family of close friends with a common love for dance and the arts. They have a stack of inborn talent for innovative choreography, effortless moves and synchronized dancing. RnG is a group of untrained dancers filled with professionalism and confidence who never fail to impress the audience with their phenomenal performances. They unite the various individual specialties giving birth to an all round breathtaking, mesmerizing and unique act each time which always getting the audiences to a roar asking for an encore. RnG believes in performing for the viewers always and pledges to win their hearts in future.

I, Azeim Malik, an ex-defense production employee (Indian Ordnance Factories & Hindustan
Aeronautics Ltd.), an Urdu Poet ( Published Poetry Books Kehna Maine Yaad Kiya Hai, Faasla
Abhi Tak Hai) & a Playwright ( Published Book Main Aadami Hoon) has a long association
with Main Stream Cinema. I started my creative innings originally as Playwright, Lyrics, Story,
Screenplay & Dialogue writer. My third Ghazal collection Rastey Nahin Milte is under
publication expected release 24 th December 2016.

I wrote two 3D Animation Films BO MAMO & AMMU-AMMU (both under production).
I did a Arabic Film SOWALIF TAFASH as Director Co-ordinate in March 2016 released on Eid in
Bahrain and All Arab. I directed the film FITRAT based on my own Story, Screenplay &
Dialogue starring Raj Kiran, Swapna, TP Jain and one more new romantic pair. It has music by
Usha Khanna, Lyrics by Nida Fazli and choreography by Saroj Khan.

An Album Kehna Maine Yaad Kiya Hai in Golden Voice of Chitra (Bombay and Tum Bin fame)
containing romantic Geet and Ghazals selected from my first Urdu Poetry Book of the same title
has been released World Wide.

In the capacity of Associate Director/Post Production Director/Chief Assistant, I worked with
prominent Film Makers, Directors and TV Producers like Asit Sen (Bairag), Chetan Anand, R K
Nayyar, Mohan Kumar, Rajesh Khanna, Desh Mukherjee, Mazhar Khan, Sagar Sarhadi, Raman
Kumar, Sameer Choudhry and Kumar Vasudeo (Humlog).

Had a brief but creatively sound spell with Gulshan Kumar & T-Series as Lyrics Coordinator and
wrote episodes of Super Hit countdown programmes Geet Bahar and Mile Sur Mera Tumhara
while simultaneously wrote Ghazals for Albums Tamanna & Ishq for T-Series, Shokhiyan for Red
Cat, Kabhie Ansoo Kabhie Khushboo Kabhie Naghma & Intezaar-e- Saba(Pankaj Udhas) for Tips
Music Company.

I penned an oriental Nautanki for Video Feature Film Banke Bihari which I directed too. I Wrote a
Mujra for Environmental Play Saare Jahan Se Achchha by Amir Raza Husain. I wrote Title
Songs for TV Serials Zeenat (UTN-Zee), Kinara Door Naheen (Lucknow DD), Miss Marry, Thoda
Sa Gham Thodi Khushi (Sony), Chatur-Moorkh (DD), Khushboo (DD Kashir) and Apna Chiraag
(DD Urdu).

Througout these 40 plus years of my Entertainment Industrys tenure, I have been actively and
honestly involved with Production side of all my programmes too. I am well conversant with almost
all financial and technical aspects of Film making like Budgeting, Scheduling, Cinematography,
Post Production/Editing and Scenario writing also.

Srivani Yalla has received much recognition for her contributions to the music world, for not only performing and teaching Carnatic Music, but also for introducing it to other art forms in the world. Today, she is one of the leading veena artists. Srivani conceives brilliant ideas and translates them into picuresque pharases of nots and it capable of carving them with exquisite craftsmanship to create a convivial atmosphere. With a subtle strum on the strings, she can produce vivacious vibrations and tenacious tones. Dignified docility despite abundant ability make here respectable and conspicuous. Being an admixture of moil, mettle and merit, Srivani had melody at her fingertips that exudes, congeals and crystalises into the specific shape of a raga which she renders.

I am a versatile artiste. A danseuse, choreographer, writer, actress, costume designer and a cultural activist. Proficient in both Kathak and Sattriya Indian classical dances, I am also a Masters in Mass Communications from Guru Jambheshwar University, Hisar (Haryana). I am also Editor of the monthly digital magazine on arts, culture and heritage named AMRAPAALI. I believes dance and Mass Communications has got a lot to do together, as both are communicative subjects and socially viable.

Born and brought up in Guwahati (Assam) and learning from a tender age of 5, I owes my first gratitude from my parents, who constantly supported me in the journey of dancing. I started learning Kathak from Guru Bipul Das and Sattriya from Guru Jibonjit Dutta. Recipient of the SCHOLARSHIP TO YOUNG ARTISTES by the Ministry of Culture, Govt. of India, My commute in dancing took different facets as I kept on exploring it.

Being an active participant from childhood, I involved myself in various platforms and brought laurels to my State. I has been honoured twice with Gold Medal for my Kathak dance, representing my State Assam at the national level for revered celebrations organised by the Govt. of India. First I won at the NATIONAL CHILDRENS FESTIVAL (1997) on eve of 50 years of Indias independence, sponsored by Department of Women and Child Development, Ministry of H.R.D., Govt. of India in collaboration with Nehru Bal Samiti. And then at the 7th NATIONAL YOUTH FESTIVAL (2002), organised by Ministry of Youth Affairs & Sports, Govt. of India, Sports & Youth Welfare Department, Govt. of Haryana and Nehru Yuva Kendra Sangathan.

I\'m a singer songwriter from Jammu. I mostly do originals and for me a song is not always about a hit chorus, sometimes its just whether it intrigues you, it holds you. I never took any singing lessons, I learned it in my room. Composing wasn\'t the part of my plan but it found its way a few years back and now it is what i do mostly. My songs can be about anything, and basically the idea is to liberate the listener and make him feel elevated.

I\'m mostly into hindi songs but sometimes, I write and sing english songs too.

and well thats it...

I am a Kirti Ramgopal, a Bharatnatyam Dancer
I began my training under Smt.Padmini Ramachandran and has also been mentored and guided by Smt. Priyadarshini Govind and Sri.A. Lakshman. Currently I am undergoing training in Abhinaya under Smt. Bragha Bessell.

With my keen ability to understand and imbibe the nuances of this beautiful art form and with my perseverance and dedication, I have traveled across India and internationally throughout US, Canada, UK, Europe, The Middle East & Bangladesh performing before discerning audiences and winning acclaim from connoisseurs of art and critics alike.

I creates incandescent Natyam with my abundance of lively skill, geometric aptness, nimbleness and grace and sensitivity in delivery. My dancing has been described as vibrant, expressive and that which extends a spirit of Joy.

It is my sincere effort to delve further into this wonderful art of Bharathanatyam and preserve and propagate its pristine beauty.

I\'m a singer songwriter from Jammu. I mostly do originals and for me a song is not always about a hit chorus, sometimes its just whether it intrigues you, it holds you. I never took any singing lessons, I learned it in my room. Composing wasn\'t the part of my plan but it found its way a few years back and now it is what i do mostly. My songs can be about anything, and basically the idea is to liberate the listener and make him feel elevated.

I\'m mostly into hindi songs but sometimes, I write and sing english songs too.

and well thats it...
